242
00:15:50,366 --> 00:15:52,725
I'll let you all introduce yourselves.

243
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:56,703
Can you help me out with something?

244
00:15:56,828 --> 00:15:57,664
Sure.

245
00:16:00,478 --> 00:16:01,834
This has to be confidential.

246
00:16:04,063 --> 00:16:05,799
I know it may seem farfetched, but

247
00:16:05,924 --> 00:16:08,045
copycat killers are not
entirely uncommon.

248
00:16:08,173 --> 00:16:10,213
This one happens to be copying
several killers.

249
00:16:10,338 --> 00:16:13,847
If he's trying to be the butcher,
why didn't he cut up and mutilate them?

250
00:16:14,057 --> 00:16:16,390
That was 7 weeks ago.
He was just getting started.

251
00:16:16,667 --> 00:16:19,637
Beginning killers are often
frightened of the crime itself.

252
00:16:19,762 --> 00:16:22,160
They're more interested in getting
it over with quickly

253
00:16:22,285 --> 00:16:23,633
and fleeing the scene.

254
00:16:23,758 --> 00:16:27,001
He was using the butcher's ruse as a way
to lure the victim to be alone with her.

255
00:16:27,126 --> 00:16:30,574
And by the time he killed Kayla,
he'd progressed. He came very close

256
00:16:30,699 --> 00:16:32,406
to copying all of the BTK's m. o.

257
00:16:32,575 --> 00:16:35,245
He's reading, learning,
borrowing from others

258
00:16:35,370 --> 00:16:36,987
because he doesn't know who he is yet.

259
00:16:37,112 --> 00:16:39,705
We think he's young and impressionable,
maybe even a student.

260
00:16:39,874 --> 00:16:41,813
Someone probably enrolled
in criminology classes.

261
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:45,127
Our technical analyst is going through
names of local students right now.

262
00:16:45,375 --> 00:16:47,208
Up to this point, changing his m.o.

263
