329
00:20:57,491 --> 00:21:00,340
We need you to write that the police
have found his signature.

330
00:21:00,535 --> 00:21:03,093
You can help us by explaining
what his signature is in your article.

331
00:21:03,299 --> 00:21:06,044
It's a killer's personal stamp,
his distinctive touch that he leaves

332
00:21:06,169 --> 00:21:07,898
at the scene of every crime.

333
00:21:08,023 --> 00:21:11,519
I've been doing this for 18 years.
And I know what a signature is, honey.

334
00:21:13,288 --> 00:21:15,439
We really need you
to be detailed about this.

335
00:21:15,608 --> 00:21:17,482
We're speaking directly to him.

336
00:21:19,036 --> 00:21:21,298
- Through my column.
- He's doing something,

337
00:21:21,561 --> 00:21:24,323
a behavioral impulse
he feels compelled to do.

338
00:21:24,689 --> 00:21:27,493
But a need-driven act
to get a sexual release

339
00:21:27,618 --> 00:21:29,734
that's specific to his psyche.

340
00:21:30,051 --> 00:21:33,071
This repetitive behavior at each
crime scene will lead us to him.

341
00:21:33,405 --> 00:21:35,155
Let me take a stab at it.

342
00:21:39,183 --> 00:21:41,023
They just found another body.

343
00:21:47,699 --> 00:21:49,640
They're bringing him up right now.

344
00:21:51,086 --> 00:21:53,352
Teenagers found him
a little over an hour ago.

345
00:21:54,884 --> 00:21:57,190
It's petechiae in the whites of his eyes.

346
00:21:58,963 --> 00:22:01,777
Judging from the bruising,
he was probably strangled with a wire.

347
00:22:02,206 --> 00:22:03,793
- Is this our guy?
- It's gotta be.

348
00:22:03,918 --> 00:22:05,871
A jogger doesn't get garroted
every day.

349
00:22:05,996 --> 00:22:08,867
Whatever signature he left was
probably washed away in the water.

350
00:22:09,313 --> 00:22:10,702
Who's he mimicking now?

351
00:22:11,060 --> 00:22:13,803
Bike path rapist Altemio Sanchez
