367
00:23:32,984 --> 00:23:34,195
Anything else in there?

368
00:23:34,320 --> 00:23:37,020
Just the notations of
an observant student.

369
00:23:37,582 --> 00:23:39,067
I've been thinking, though.

370
00:23:39,192 --> 00:23:41,430
Zoe got all of her information
from the newspapers

371
00:23:41,555 --> 00:23:43,253
and from Paula McConnell's column.

372
00:23:43,422 --> 00:23:46,387
There's no way she could have known
about every homicide in the city.

373
00:23:46,512 --> 00:23:48,383
Not every homicide's
reported in the papers.

374
00:23:48,552 --> 00:23:51,595
So how do we know he didn't commit more
murders than the ones in her journals?

375
00:23:51,764 --> 00:23:52,680
We don't.

376
00:23:53,102 --> 00:23:55,223
We can check missing
persons and see if anyone

377
00:23:55,392 --> 00:23:57,843
was last seen
in the unsub's operating zone.

378
00:24:00,731 --> 00:24:01,689
What?

379
00:24:01,814 --> 00:24:04,256
Well, a young person's
mind is so active...

380
00:24:04,381 --> 00:24:07,277
yours, Zoe's,
and I imagine this unsub's, too.

381
00:24:07,796 --> 00:24:10,781
I think when we get him, he'll be
curious. He'll ask questions.

382
00:24:11,687 --> 00:24:13,201
Rossi, heads up. She knows.

383
00:24:15,491 --> 00:24:16,661
Did you do this?

